result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (3rd) and Operating w/ PAC (3rd). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (3rd) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (3rd) was dismissed by the court.

  • Chase A Bryant was found guilty of Vehicle Operator Flee/Elude Officer, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.04(3).
  • Chase A Bryant was found guilty of OWI (3rd), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Chase A Bryant in court with attorney Jamie J LaVora.  Barbara A. Michaels appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Counts 1 & 2.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Count 3 dismissed and read in.  Count 4 dismissed by operation of law.  Case 14TR6407 dismissed and read in to this matter.  

Court orders the following:

Count 1:
- Sentence withheld
- 2 years 6 months Probation. 
- Court costs of $268.00 to be paid as a Condition of Probation
- DNA Surcharge of $250.00 to be paid as a Condition of Probation
- DNA Sample required
- Conditions of Probation:  Maintain absolute sobriety/Random UAs.  No use or possession of alcohol/drug paraphernalia/drugs without a valid prescription.  Valid prescriptions to be taken in the manner they were prescribed.  Maintain full-time employment and/or school.  Continue with current treatment.
CONDITION TIME: 90 days - NON WORKING HOURS WITH STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS - CONSECUTIVE to condition time in Count 2.  Court would allow for extended hours - 15 hours each on Tuesday and Thursday to accommodate work and school.

Count 2:
- Sentence withheld
- 1 year Probation
- 30 months Drivers License Revocation. 
- 30 months Ignition Interlock on any vehicle TITLED OR REGISTERED to defendant 
- Alcohol Assessment
- Attendance at the Victim Impact Panel meeting already completed
- Fine of $1494.00; cash bail to be applied.  Any remaining fine to be paid as a Condition of Probation
- Blood Test Reimbursement of $50.00 paid through Waukesha County Circuit Court to be forwarded to Waukesha County Sheriff's Department
- DNA Surcharge waived
- DNA Sample waived
- Conditions of Probation: Same as Count 1
CONDITION TIME: 45 days - NON WORKING HOURS WITH STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS - To commence FORTHWITH.  Court would allow for extended hours - 15 hours each on Tuesday and Thursday to accommodate work and school.
